OL,4,CCity Council
OL,6,FGMB's Megan Fisher said: "This
OL,7,Fagreement has been hard won by the
OL,8,Fwomen workers of Birmingham. After
OL,9,Fyears of discrimination and being paid
OL,10,Fless than they were worth, they stood
OL,11,Fup and demanded what was theirs.
OL,13,F"Public bodies cannot run from the
OL,14,Fmistakes of the past; they must
OL,15,Fconfront and fix them. GMB welcomes
OL,16,Ftoday's historic step, as well as the
OL,17,Fconstructive approach to negotiations
OL,18,Ffrom Councillor John Cotton and others
OL,19,Fin recent months.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUuD@AOU
